<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<!-- @include components/_head.kit -->
<body>
	<style>
		body {
			background: #161616;
			color: #F5F5F7;
		}
		a {
			text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
		}
		.yellow-link {
			text-decoration-color: #FFBD21;
		}
		.yellow-link:hover {
			color: #FFBD21;
			text-decoration-color: #FFBD21;
		}
		.pink-link {
			text-decoration-color: #BE1473;
		}
		.pink-link:hover {
			color: #BE1473;
			text-decoration-color: #BE1473;
		}
		.green-link {
			text-decoration-color: #15BF5F;
		}
		.green-link:hover {
			color: #15BF5F;
			text-decoration-color: #15BF5F;
		}
		.text-svg {
			
		}
	</style>
	
	<header style="background-color: #161616;">
		<nav>
			<a href="/" class="bold-900" style="text-decoration-color: #4c4c4f; color: #a1a1a6 !important;">Dillon J. Brown</a>
			<a href="mailto:hello@dillonbrown.me" style="text-decoration-color: #4c4c4f; color: #a1a1a6 !important;">Contact</a>
			<a href="/pdf/resume.pdf" style="text-decoration-color: #4c4c4f; color: #a1a1a6 !important;">Résumé</a>
		</nav>
	</header>
	
	<!--
		MOBILE AUDIO APPS
	-->
	<section>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="twelve columns">
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_text-mobile-audio-ui.svg -->
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="row">
			<div class="eight offset-by-four columns">
				<p style="font-size: 2rem; color: #a1a1a6; margin-top: 4rem;">There are more music apps than ever. However, few of them are made for people like me. Instead of renting music from Spotify, I buy my own copy from sites like Bandcamp. Additionally, I have other kinds of audio files, like audiobooks, stand-up comedy albums, and epic longform podcasts no longer in a feed.</p>
				<p style="font-size: 2rem; color: #a1a1a6;">I want to make a suite of apps laser-focused on one medium each. I envision these audio apps sharing a codebase for much of their functionality and similar interfaces, each tailored to their content.</p>
			</div>
		</div>	
	</section>

	
	<!--
		TOUCH TARGETS
	-->
	<div class="row" style="background: #EFEFF4; padding: 0 0 5rem 0;box-shadow: inset 0 9px 30px -10px rgba(217,217,217,1);;">
		<section>
			<div class="ten offset-by-one columns">
				<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/mobile-audio-ui/phone-scrubber.png" alt="" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
			</div>
			<div class="ten offset-by-one columns center">
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_text-lets-talk.svg -->
				<p style="font-size: 2rem; color: #161616;">My design introduces a large, finger-friendly scrubber. Grab the waveform from any location and slide horizontally to change your place in a song.</p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
	<div class="row" style="background: #EFEFF4; padding: 0 0 5rem 0; margin-bottom: 0;">
		<section>
			<div class="six columns center">
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_touch-targets.svg -->
				<p style="color: #161616;">A large touch target makes for easy one-handed use with any grip.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="six columns center">
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_touch-targets-2.svg -->
				<p style="color: #161616;"><a class="green-link" href="https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/ios/visual-design/adaptivity-and-layout/">Apple's Human Interface Guidelines</a> suggest a minimum size of 44pt for interactive elements. Most popular apps don't even come close.</p>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
	
	<!--
		GESTURES?
	-->
	<div class="row" style="color: #161616; background-color: white">
		<section style="padding: 5rem 0 5rem 0;">
			<div class="ten offset-by-one center columns">
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_text-gestures.svg -->
				<p style="font-size: 2rem;">Gestures pack in more functionality without sacrificing screen space. However, they can be hard to find. In my design gestures are an additional way to use the interface, not the only way.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="row">
				<div class="twelve columns">
					<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/mobile-audio-ui/gesture.png" alt="">
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
	
	
	<!--
		BIG OL' BUTTONS
	-->
	<div class="row" style="background: #EFEFF4; color: #161616">
		<section>
			<div class="six columns" style="padding: 15rem 0 0 0;">
				<!-- @include components/mobile-audio-ui/_text-big-buttons.svg -->
				<p style="font-size: 2rem;">The music app gets an option for even bigger buttons. Tap on the artwork to play/pause your music. Swipe left and right to change tracks.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="six columns">
				<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/mobile-audio-ui/buttons.png" alt="">
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>
</body>
</html>